title: kempf_(fire_emblem)
body:
Class: [b]Mage Knight[/b]

Boss character from [[Fire Emblem: Thracia 776]]. Descendant of the Friege bloodline and a commander in Friege's army occupying the lands of Thracia, he possesses minor Thrud blood.

Kempf is a haughty and self-aggrandizing man who belittles and intimidates those below his standing. Despises [[Reinhardt (Fire Emblem)|Reinhardt]] for the latter's superior proficiency despite possessing no Holy Blood, and takes that frustration out on Reinhardt's sister, [[Olwen (Fire Emblem)|Olwen]].

Kempf coined the franchise archetype of the cocky enemy general whose defeat grants the player a great deal of satisfaction and catharsis. Furthermore, an old (mis)translation meme revolves around him saying "In America!" without any context.

title: banya_(sauna)
body:
A banya (Russian: баня, IPA: [ˈbanʲə] (About this soundlisten)) is originally a Slavic steam bath with a stove. It is considered an important part of Russian culture with Slavic roots. The bath takes place in a small room or building designed for dry or wet heat sessions. The steam and high heat make the bathers perspire.

In the Russian language, the word banya may also refer to a public bathhouse, most historically famous being the Sanduny (Sandunovskie bani).

title: moetan
body:
MOETAN stands for Methodology Of English, The Academic Necessity. Moetan is an English language study for Japanese otaku. The sentences used to describe English words are somewhat... just wrong. Take for instance: Priest – “the priest has a cross-shaped bazooka.” That has a high wtf factor. This is also an anime series with some new characters.

h6. Characters

    * [[Nao-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Nijihara Ink]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Pastel Ink]]   -   ELS, TV (Nijahara Ink's magical girl form)
    * [[Ah-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Pen-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Oni-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Kuroi Sumi]]   -   TV
    * [[Tempera Sumi]]  -  TV (Kuroi Sumi's magical girl form)
    * [[Ka-kun]]   -   TV
    * [[Shiratori Arisu]]   -   TV
    * [[Na-kun]]   -   TV
    * [[Ruriko]]   -   TV
    * [[Mio Teduka]]   -   TV
    * [[Remi Suzuki]]   -   TV
    * [[Rina Tanaka]]   -   TV
    * [[Rihoko Furuta]]   -   TV
    * [[Majimero]]   -   TV

h6. Examples

* Disappoint - “in my childhood I was cruelly disappointed at the sight of the slide fasteners on the back of the heroes.”
* Priest – “the priest has a cross-shaped bazooka.”
* Object – “he obstinately refuses to accept that rosebud games contain sexual objects.’
* Expensive - “dahhhh!! Don’t launch lots of expensive missiles too quickly!’
* Decide – ‘let’s decide the supremacy of the Earth by the blows of robots.’
* Request – ‘the red queen requested them to strike his head off.’
* Strict – ‘the strict procedure is required to recall the dragon.’
* Broadcast – ‘they broadcast the scene of glance at the panties of the national icon.’
* Preserve – ‘the overexploitation of ears and foxtails caused so much controversy so they established a place to preserve it.;’
* Crush – ‘the steps the giant hero takes when he doges the attack crushes the neighboring houses. We must remember that.’
* Assist- ‘are you assisted by the amazing-shocking mechanics of this week?’
* Arrest – ‘the mad scientist was arrested for attempted earth destruction.’
* Scare – ‘the angel who lives on his house scared him, because she beat him to death without notice.’
* Imply – ‘an occupation of ‘job-hoping part-time worker’ implies a state of unemployment.’
* Distinguish – ‘it is difficult to distinguish the Chinese noodle man from the Mongol man.’
* Apologize – ‘the newspaper publisher apologizes for getting someone angered with elaborate dishes.’
* Embarrass – ‘ the wrong use of the magic equipment often embarrasses the girl in the bathroom while she is taking a bath.’
* Pollution – ‘the degree of mental pollution is rising up to level E! we can’t wait!’
* Beat – ‘i’ll never stop beating you until you cry.’
* Exist – ‘how many times do I have to say that people who live in the earth never exist?’
* Rational – ‘earth persons are sometimes irritated by the rational judgement of the space alien’s with sharp shaped ears.’
* Subscribe-‘ I subscribed my name to the contract with the witch. And I had a job in the public bath.’

title: yc9
body:
The name given to the second, succeeding generation design of the Hi-Point C-9, decided by way of an online contest. The "YC" stands for "Yeet Cannon", meant to represent the meme status of Hi-Point's weaponry among firearms enthusiasts.

The naming contest generated a significant amount of controversy when Hi-Point did not include the name among the list of finalists, until pressure from social media and even Heckler & Koch (who even promised to do a collaborative photoshoot with them and their new gun, bringing a Mark 23 specifically marked as the YC-45) finally forced them to give in. The name "YC-9" was pitted against the other finalists and ultimately won, with the new YC-9 set to release in late 2019, with a special C-9 YCG1 being sold to commemorate the occasion.

English name: [b]Arfoire[/b] (a reference to the "R4 flash cartridge":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R4_cartridge)

The main antagonist of [[Choujigen Game Neptune]], Magiquone is a woman of high expectations, and tolerates no failures. She has appeared as "The Overlord's Messenger" and as Evangelist/Conversation while in Leanbox or Lowee. Magiquone's ambitions were to destroy Gamindustri and become the True Goddess, though she was stopped cold in her tracks by [[neptune_(choujigen_game_neptune)|Neptune]] and company. A criminal organization seeks the revival of Magiquone in the sequel, [[Choujigen Game Neptune mk2]].

Magiquone was once friends with [[Histoire]], but she turned against her when Gamindustri was split into four.

Voiced by: Takahashi Chiaka (Japanese), [[Laura Post]] (English)

title: shakti_(elsword)
body:
[[Ara Haan]]'s third character class following [[asura (elsword)|Asura]]. On the Korean server, this class' name references [b]Shiva[/b].

[i]Shakti[/i] is a divine feminine entity in Hinduism, and the supreme being in Shaktism. [i]Shiva[/i] is part of the Hindu Trimurti alongside Brahma and Vishnu.

title: asura_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[shakti (elsword)|Shakti]]. She keeps her hair down, has white streaks added, and wears a white-and-black bow. Her eyes now have [[heterochromia]], with one being red and the other yellow. She wears a sheer top with [[detached sleeves]], a white skirt, toeless [[ankle wrap]]s, and has multiple pieces of cloth tied with [[jingle bell]]s.

Asura's name refers to a member of a class of divine beings in the Vedic period, which in Indian mythology tend to be evil, while in Zoroastrianism, they are benevolent.

title: little_specter_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes. She has her hair tied into [[twin braids]] and sports an [[ahoge]]. Her eyes now have [[heterochromia]], with one eye red and the other yellow. She wears a sheer top with [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[juliet sleeves]], a red [[corset]], a [[black skirt]], white [[ankle wrap|ankle wraps]] and black [[clog sandals]].

While the word [i]specter[/i] refers to a ghost, this class revolves around Ara's transformation into a nine-tailed [i]youkai[/i], or a supernatural monster from Japanese mythology.

title: devi_(elsword)
body:
[[Ara Haan]]'s third character class following [[yama raja (elsword)|Yama Raja]]. Be careful not to confuse this class' design with Yama Raja's since they appear very similar. This class has a long [[black dress]] with a distinct [[side slit]] that shows her legs. This class also has a single [[pantyhose]] covering her entire left leg, whereas Yama Raja's left leg has a [[single thighhigh]].

This class was originally called [b]Brahman Samraat[/b], intended to refer to the Hindu god Brahmadeva, but caused confusion due to an Indian mathematician sharing the same name. The class name was changed to [b]Devi[/b], which is a feminine form of the goddess that is referred to as "heavenly, divine and anything of excellence" in Hindu culture.

title: yama_raja_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes. She ties her hair in a low ponytail and has some [[hairpin]]s on her bangs. She wears an [[asymmetrical clothes|asymmetrical costume]] consisting of long [[black gloves]], a single sleeve on her left arm, a black [[feather boa]], a black-and-white [[miniskirt]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]] with a [[single thighhigh|black single thighhigh]] on her left leg.

Be careful not to confuse this class' character design with [[devi (elsword)|Devi]]'s design since they are very similar. This class has a black-and-white dress that only reaches her waist, and she has a [[single thighhigh]] covering her left leg here, whereas Devi has a single [[pantyhose]] covering her entire left leg instead.

The Japanese name for this class is [i]Meiou[/i] (冥王) or "King of the Dead," and the term [i]yama[/i] refers to the judge of the dead and ruler of the Narakas in Buddhist and Hindu mythology.

title: marisha_(fire_emblem)
body:
Character in [[Fire Emblem: Mystery of the Emblem]] and [[Fire Emblem: New Mystery of the Emblem]]. Has a minor appearance in [[Fire Emblem Heroes]].

She is claimed to only be nine years old by her grandmother so she isn't captured by Lang and his men, but she has come of age. Her grandmother offers her to [[Marth (fire emblem)|]] as his bride (not knowing he already has a fiancée, [[Caeda (fire emblem)|]]), to which Marisha is unsure, as it is far too soon. In the remake, she fawns over Marth.

Officially romanized as [b]Malliesia[/b] in [[Fire Emblem: New Mystery of the Emblem]] and as [b]Marisha[/b] in [[Fire Emblem Heroes]]. Unofficially romanized as [b]Malicia[/b] in the [i]New Mystery of the Emblem[/i] fan translation patch.

title: fado_(fire_emblem)
body:
A character from [[Fire Emblem: The Sacred Stones]].

The king of Renais, and the father of the twins [[Eirika (fire emblem)|]] and [[Ephraim (fire emblem)|]]. He was known as the valiant Warrior King in his time. During the prologue of the game, Fado is killed in a raid on Renais Castle, forcing his daughter to flee with the knight [[Seth (Fire Emblem)|]].

Fado can be unlocked as a playable General in the Creature Campaign postgame mode.

In [[Fire Emblem Heroes]], Brave Ephraim dons his father's armor.

title: karel_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Karel[/b] is a character from [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]] and [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]].

One of few characters who has a playable appearance in both titles, Karel's personality drastically differs between the games. [[Karla (Fire Emblem)|] is his sister, [[Bartre (Fire Emblem)|]] his brother-in-law, and [[Fir (Fire Emblem)|]], his niece.

In [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]], Karel is a bloodthirsty warrior who will stop at nothing to sate his bloodlust, to the point where he is better known by his moniker of [i]Sword Demon[/i]. He can be recruited instead of [[Harken (Fire Emblem)|]] depending on the conditions met during the chapter.

Twenty years later, in [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]], Karel appears as an endgame recruit in Chapter 23, and only Fir and Bartre are capable of recruiting him, convincing Karel to fight alongside his family one more time. Now much older, Karel has significantly calmed down and appears almost as though he were a different person altogether. He serves as a mentor for other characters, and shares a brotherly bond with his brother-in-law Bartre.

Following the end of the Disturbance of Bern, Karel retreats back to his village in Bern, where junior swordfighters learn the path of the sword, guided by his indirect mentoring.

Class: [b]Swordmaster[/b] (both appearances)

title: roulette
body:
A [[casino]] game named after the French word meaning [i]little wheel[/i]. In the game, players may choose to place bets on either a single number or a range of numbers, the colors red or black, or whether the number is odd or even, or if the numbers are high (19-36) or low (1-18)

To determine the winning number and color, a croupier (dealer) spins a wheel in one direction, then spins a ball in the opposite direction around a tilted circular track running around the circumference of the wheel. The ball eventually loses momentum and falls onto the wheel and into one of 37 (in French/European roulette) or 38 (in American roulette) colored and numbered pockets on the wheel. Payouts range from 35:1 for a single number bet down to 1:1 for an odd/even or red/black bet.

h4.See also

title: jane_maxwell
body:
Character in [i][[Wild Arms 1]][/i], also known as Calamity Jane. Jane also makes a cameo in [[Wild Arms 5]]. She is always seen with her butler [[Magdalen Harts]]. Her real name is Jane Maxwell, though she has no direct relation to [[Virginia Maxwell]], the protagonist of [i][[Wild Arms 3]][/i]. 'Calamity Jane' is a nickname based off a real historical figure named Martha Jane Cannary Burke.

Jane initially is a 'rival' to [[Rody Roughnight]]'s party as she hunts for treasure, but is actually trying to save her family orphanage in Court Seim. As she learns more about the group, she becomes friendlier with them and even develops feelings for Rody. While she joins the party in certain storyline moments, she can be picked up as a permanent member later.

In [i]Wild Arms 3[/i], [[Maya Schrodinger]] greatly resembles Jane, both in appearance and personality.  This is because Maya has the ability to mimic the abilities of characters from books she reads, and she particularly enjoys one called "Disaster Girl of the Wasteland," the title character of which is strongly implied to be Jane.

title: kieran_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Kieran[/b] (ケビン) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the sub-commander of the Crimean Royal Knights, and serves under General [[geoffrey_(fire_emblem)|Geoffrey]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Axe Knight (Path of Radiance), Axe Paladin (Radiant Dawn).

title: pelleas_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Pelleas[/b] (ペレアス) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is believed to be the son of [[Ashnard (fire emblem)|Ashnard]] and the Prince of Daein. He has a strong devotion to his country and desires to free it from oppression by the Begnion Occupational Army. Pelleas acts as a figurehead for the Daein Liberation Army, which he entrusts [[micaiah (fire emblem)|Micaiah]] to lead in his stead as the commanding general.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Dark Sage

title: volug_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Volug[/b] (オルグ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Volug is Queen [[Nailah (fire emblem)|Nailah]]'s retainer. He is a Wolf Laguz, hailing from the lost nation of Hatari.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Wolf

title: skrimir_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Skrimir[/b] (スクリミル) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the nephew of Gallia's King [[caineghis (fire emblem)|Caineghis]]. He commands the Laguz Alliance in the war with Begnion. He was named Caineghis' successor.

He is voiced by Tanzawa Teruyuki in the cutscenes.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Lion

title: rolf_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Rolf[/b] (ヨファ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the youngest member of the Greil Mercenaries and the younger brother of [[Oscar (fire emblem)|Oscar]] and [[Boyd (fire emblem)|Boyd]]. He is a mature, loyal young man. He was first taught how to use a bow by [[shinon_(fire_emblem)|Shinon]], so that, like [[mist_(fire_emblem)|Mist]], he could be of some use to the group rather than staying behind every time the company went to work.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Archer (Path of Radiance), Sniper (Radiant Dawn)

title: calill_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Calill[/b] (カリル) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is the wife of the Berserker [[largo_(fire_emblem)|Largo]] and a surrogate mother for their adopted child Amy. Calill and [[largo_(fire_emblem)|Largo]] also run a bar in Crimea, and are close friends with Queen [[elincia_ridell_crimea|Elincia]] and the Crimean Royal Knights.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Sage (Path of Radiance), Fire Sage (Radiant Dawn).

title: nolan_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Nolan[/b] (ノイス) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He is the official leader of the Dawn Brigade, although [[micaiah (fire emblem)|Micaiah]] usually acts as such throughout the story. He is the oldest member of the Dawn Brigade, and acts like a father figure to best friends [[edward_(fire_emblem)|Edward]] and [[leonardo_(fire_emblem)|Leonardo]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Fighter

title: tauroneo_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Tauroneo[/b] (タウロニオ) is a playable character that appears in [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Tauroneo comes from a renowned military family in Daein. Tauroneo was once one of Daein's steadfast Four Riders. He shared that title with Gawain, Lanvega, and Bryce.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: General (Path of Radiance), Lance General (Radiant Dawn).

title: brom_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Brom[/b] (チャップ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He hails from the farming village of Ohma, which is also the hometown of [[Nephenee (fire emblem)|Nephenee]], and lives with a large family that consists of many children. Brom is the father of [[meg_(fire_emblem)|Meg]].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Knight (Path of Radiance), Axe General (Radiant Dawn).

title: meg_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Meg[/b] (メグ) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

Meg is the daughter of [[brom (fire emblem)|Brom]]. Meg originally joins the Dawn Brigade hoping that she will 'meet her future husband' that her father told her to seek out.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Armor Sword

title: aran_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Aran[/b] (ブラッド) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

He was initially a soldier fighting with the Begnion Occupational Army in Daein, but later joins the Dawn Brigade and the Daein Liberation Army.
Aran is a childhood friend of [[laura (fire emblem)|Laura]],having lived in Kisca with her for a good part of his early life.

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Soldier

title: moped
body:
A type of low-powered [[motorcycle]] that uses bicycle pedals to assist the engine with hill-climbing and pedaling away from a stationary position. The term [i]moped[/i] originates from the Swedish words [i][b]mo[/b]tor[/i] and [i][b]ped[/b]aler[/i]. Some mopeds have a step-through design (post #1132037) while others use a conventional motorcycle frame (post #689998). At the lighter end of the scale, there is some overlap between mopeds and motorized [[bicycle|bicycles]].

Some regional governments classify motor scooters as mopeds based on factors such as engine displacement or speed. As these rules vary between jurisdictions and vehicle performance can not always be ascertained based on artwork, two-wheeled motor vehicles with a step-through design but without pedals should always be tagged [[scooter]] instead.

A character from [[Cygames]]'s [i][[Shingeki no Bahamut]][/i] and a card in [i][[Shadowverse]][/i], as well as a playable character in [i][[Granblue Fantasy]][/i] where she is known as Orchid.

In [i][[Shingeki no Bahamut]][/i], Orchis is a miraculous doll created with a heart, and she travels the world with her golem [[lloyd_(granblue_fantasy)|Lloyd]], a gift from her deceased creator. 

In [i][[Granblue Fantasy]][/i], Orchid is the empty shell of a personality left behind when the princess of Erste, [[queen_orchis|Orchis]], was separated from her body. She would eventually receive a golem body of her own along with [[lloyd_(granblue_fantasy)|Lloyd]], a golem that holds a powerful primal beast within itself.

Orchis looks like a young girl with long, silver blue hair typically tied in twintails. She has doll joints (except when depicted within [[queen_orchis|Granblue Fantasy Orchis]]'s body), a frilled black dress, elbow gloves, and a mini hat. She usually has a little tiger doll with a top hat by her side.

title: c2_kikan
body:
C2 Kikan (Japanese: C2機関/株式会社C2プレパラート (C2 Präparat Inc.)), alternatively translated as "C2 Architecture", "Contents Communication Architecture", and aka "KanColle Unei Chinjufu", is a doujin circle, who is one of the copyright holders of the [[Kantai Collection]] -KanColle- brand.

C2 Kikan debuted in Comiket C75 (Winter 2008) with a doujin about food, introducing various types of food through anime personifications. They were interviewed by various TV programs for it at the time, including タモリ倶楽部 from Asahi TV and MAG・ネット from NHK. They later published several military-related doujinshi.

It's possible that the name of 'C2 Kikan' came from Final Fantasy: Unlimited, where Tanaka Kensuke, one of the main members of C2 Kikan, was the anime's general producer for, when he worked in Square Soft back in 2001.

When Tanaka Kensuke and his friend, who was working within Kadokawa Games talked with Michio Okamiya, whom he once worked with back in Square Soft, they came up with the idea of the KanColle browser game.

(Source: "KanColle Wiki":https://kancolle.fandom.com/wiki/C2_Kikan)

Official website: http://www.c2architecture.com/
Official twitter: https://twitter.com/C2_STAFF

Felicita is the only character in the game so far to have two Arcanas, the Amanti and the La Ruota Della Fortuna.

Felicita is almost always seen wearing a [[skirt suit]] with an [[underbust]] belt, complemented with thigh-high socks, a white belt on the left legs, and black high heel [[knee boots]]. Her combat style prioritizes the usage of daggers and kicks.

Voiced by [[Noto Mamiko]].

title: jack_daniel's
body:
Jack Daniel's is a brand of Tennessee whiskey and the top-selling American whiskey in the world. It is produced in Lynchburg, Tennessee, by the Jack Daniel Distillery, which has been owned by the Brown–Forman Corporation since 1956.

Packaged in square bottles, Jack Daniel's "Black Label" Tennessee whiskey sold 12.5 million cases in 2017. Other brand variations, such as Tennessee Honey, Gentleman Jack, and Tennessee Fire, added another 2.9 million cases to sales. Sales of an additional 800,000 equivalent cases in ready-to-drink (RTD) products brought the fiscal year total to more than 16.1 million equivalent adjusted cases for the entire Jack Daniel's family of brands. 

Jack Daniel's home county of Moore is a dry county, so the product is not available for purchase at stores or restaurants within the county.

body:

body:

body:
An 1814 oil painting by Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres depicting a [[nude]] concubine [[reclining]] on her side as seen from behind. title: domon_kasshu
body:
The protagonist of [[G Gundam]]. Domon is a powerful martial artist, but lacks much in the name of any other skills. His engineer and childhood friend is [[Rain Mikamura]], and he pilots the [[Shining Gundam]] and later [[God Gundam]], representing Neo Japan.

Voiced by [[Seki Tomokazu]] (JP) and Mark Gatha (EN).

title: ritsu_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character.

The second eldest of the sisters split off from the First Person, behind [[ryou (kemurikusa)|Ryou]]. She embodies the sense of Hearing. She enjoys taking care of [[midori (kemurikusa)|Midori]], a large Kemurikusa plant which she has control over, that carries the subway car which the main character group travels in. She ends all her sentences with a verbal tic of "nya", a habit formed for the sake of lightening [[rin (kemurikusa)|Rin's]] mood.

title: shiro_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character.

A collection of robots that was created to take orders from [[wakaba (kemurikusa)|Wakaba]]. It communicates in Katakana through a screen that displays text, with very simple syntax.

title: rina_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character. 

The youngest of the six sisters split off from the First Person, embodying the sense of Taste. She is distinguished by her ability to eat anything and create copies of herself after consuming enough material. She ends all her sentences with a verbal tic of "na". [spoiler] Originally Rina had seven copies of herself, but three of them died; one in the first half of the series, and the other two offscreen and pre-story. [/spoiler]

title: riri_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character.

[spoiler]The First Person (最初の人), from whom all the sisters sprouted from. Originally a human, She had drowned to death when [[wakaba (kemurikusa)|Wakaba]] found her. Wakaba brought her back to life using Midori and took her into his care. She was accidentally responsible for creating the red Kemurikusa that corrupts the machines inside the ship.[/spoiler]

title: ryou_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character. The eldest of the six main sisters. 

She embodies the sense of smell and was one of the main fighters of the group until she was believed to have died. Her eyes are [[closed eyes|always closed]].

title: wakaba_(kemurikusa)
body:
[i][[Kemurikusa]][/i] character. A naive and childish new addition to [[rin (kemurikusa)|Rin]]'s party, always curious about [[kemurikusa_(object)|kemurikusa]]. His origins are unknown.

[spoiler]Previously a white coat wearing researcher who sacrificed himself to save Riri, however he used Midori to create a new copy of himself after death. His rebirth led to his name going from katakana to hiragana.[/spoiler]

title: relena_peacecraft
body:
Character from [[Gundam Wing]]. Relena is initially a normal school-age girl - however, a series of chance meetings with (unbeknownst to her) Gundam pilot [[Heero Yuy]] sends her life into a crazy spiral. She has [[long_hair|long]] light [[brown hair]], and somewhat of a disposition to get herself in situations where she could possibly be killed - sometimes daring Heero to do so. 

[spoiler]While Relena initially believes her father to be Prime Minister Darlian, he reveals in his deathbed that she is indeed the younger daughter of King Peacecraft, and the younger sister of [[Zechs Merquise]].[/spoiler]

title: chang_wufei
body: One of the Gundam pilots from [[gundam_wing|New Mobile Report Gundam Wing]]. Wufei is a Chinese boy with [[black hair]] usually kept in a short [[ponytail]]. His arrogant, condescending and at times outright abusive tone makes him an easy target for furious enemies - however, his absolutely crushing skill at the controls of the mighty [[Shenlong Gundam]] is sure to discourage the less brave from challenging the cocky fighter.

title: quatre_raberba_winner
body: One of the Gundam pilots in [[gundam wing|New Mobile Report Gundam Wing]]. Quatre (French for "four") is a young, blond-haired boy with a kind heart and a gentle disposition. Despite his frail and tender looks, his skill when piloting the fierce [[Gundam Sandrock]] terrified anyone who was unlucky enough to cross paths with him in the battlefield.

title: gundam_sandrock
body:
[b]XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock[/b] 
The personal machine of [[Quatre Raberba Winner]], this Gundam was created to serve as a command unit, leading both the Gundams and Quatre's loyal Maganac Corps. The unit was exceptional in desert operations, built tough as nails (even more heavily armored than the other Gundams), and its massive heat shotels could tear enemy mobile suits to shreds in close combat.

title: shining_gundam

title: shigofumi
body:
Shigofumi (シゴフミ ~Stories of Last Letter~) is a series of 12 episodes fantasy anime directed by Tatsuo Satou, aired between January and March 2008. There's also a light novel of the same series, released before the anime in October 2006, but considered a consequent work, as the project of this anime has afore been commenced.

The story, as titled, focuses on supernatural events that occurs on many dead people who reached afterlife, which allow them to send something, mostly letters that contain unexpressed feeling when they were alive, to anyone in the living world via "shigofumi." Dead youths in uniform, each wielding an AI implemented staff as aid granter, are used in carrying tasks. To every individual carrier has their own specific area of work on the world but shares the same workplace when not out for delivering, in another realm called Shigo.

Fumika, a young early teenage girl and the female protagonist, takes part in the story as another carrier of shigofumi. She hides her past behind from her little society, but the only thing that remains obviously doubtful is her normally flowing age, which is supposed to stop when she died and became a shigofumi carrier, like every others.

body:
Real Name: SST Laboratories Siege Automaton E54
Age: 30
Occupation: Battle Automaton

A defense-class character in [[Overwatch]].
